SHIELDS v. WARDEN OF MARYLAND HOUSE OF CORRECTION [P. C. No. 5,

September Term, 1959 (Adv.).]

Decided July 6, 1959.

*662Before Bruñe, C. J., and Henderson, Hammond, Prescott and Horney, JJ.

PER Curiam.

Petitioner’s application for leave to appeal under the Post Conviction Procedure Act is denied for the reasons set out by the court below.

Application denied.
